{
  "doc_id": "49914",
  "text": "Recently, robots especially the human-support robots are sincerely requested to be developed for practical applications such as nursing care of patient, holding objects and machine operation [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Many sensors are used to inspect the condition of the objects for robot operation, and especially tactile sensor is useful to ideatify the position and mechanical condition. So, tactile sensing is very important to assure the safety of human body and accurate control and various tactile sensors for the robots have been proposed [CITATION_3] - [CITATION_4] . However, micro and integrated tactile sensor, which can simultaneously detect normal and shear stresses, have not been developed so well yet.",
